y (Australian politician)|Thomas Murphy]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Concord|Concord]] ||  1953\u20131968\n|-\n|| [[George Neilly]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Cessnock|Cessnock]] || 1959\u20131978\n|-\n|| [[Leo Nott]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Mudgee|Mudgee]] || 1953\u20131973\n|-\n|| Hon [[Roger Nott]] {{ref label|7|7|7}} || Labor || [[Electoral district of Liverpool Plains|Liverpool Plains]] || 1941-1961\n|-\n|| [[Frank O'Keefe]] {{ref label|7|7|7}} || Country || [[Electoral district of Liverpool Plains|Liverpool Plains]] || 1961\u20131969\n|-\n|| [[Doug Padman]] || Liberal || [[Electoral district of Albury|Albury]] || 1947-1965\n|-\n|| [[Spence Powell]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Bankstown|Bankstown]] || 1950-1962\t\n|-\n|| [[Leon Punch]] || Country || [[Electoral district of Upper Hunter|Upper Hunter]] || 1959\u20131985\n|-\n|| [[Frank Purdue]] || Independent || [[Electoral district of Waratah (New South Wales)|Waratah]] || 1956\u20131962, 1964-1965\n|-\n|| Hon [[Jack Renshaw]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Castlereagh|Castlereagh]] || 1941\u20131980\n|-\n|| [[Bill Rigby (politician)|Bill Rigby]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Hurstville|Hurstville]] || 1959-1965\n|-\n|| [[Ian Robinson (Australian politician)|Ian Robinson]] || Country || [[Electoral district of Casino|Casino]] || 1953-1963\n|-\n|| [[Jim Robson (politician)|Jim Robson]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Hartley (New South Wales)|Hartley]] || 1956-1965\n|-\n|| Hon [[Norm Ryan]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Marrickville|Marrickville]] || 1953\u20131973\n|-\n|| [[Thomas Ryan (New South Wales politician)|Thomas Ryan]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Auburn|Auburn]] || 1956-1965\n|-\n|| [[John Seiffert]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Monaro|Monaro]] || 1941-1965\n|-\n|| Hon [[Bill Sheahan (politician)|Bill Sheahan]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Burrinjuck|Burrinjuck]] || 1941\u20131973\n|-\n|| [[Jim Simpson (Australian politicia